Ever since the Green New Deal landed on the political map, liberals have attacked it for its supposedly impractical scope and ambition.
Conservative Chico city council members have gone on the offensive against the Green New Deal with precisely this kind of attack.
Thanks in large part to these grassroots activists, the evacuees who ended up at the Chico Walmart were greeted with clothing, pollution masks, hot meals, dog food, and much more.
Which brings us back to the Chico Green New Deal and its plan for green jobs, public transit, local food, reduced car traffic, and more affordable housing.